{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":380,"text":"So, before I became a dermatologist,"},{"time":2787,"text":"I started in general medicine,"},{"time":5339,"text":"as most dermatologists do in Britain."},{"time":7555,"text":"At the end of that time, I went off to Australia,"},{"time":9603,"text":"about 20 years ago."},{"time":11499,"text":"What you learn when you go to Australia"},{"time":13620,"text":"is the Australians are very competitive."},{"time":16346,"text":"And they are not magnanimous in victory."},{"time":18403,"text":"And that happened a lot:"},{"time":20467,"text":"\"You pommies, you can't play cricket, rugby.\""},{"time":22899,"text":"I could accept that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25017,"text":"But moving into work --"},{"time":27347,"text":"and we have each week what's called a journal club,"},{"time":29885,"text":"when you'd sit down with the other doctors"},{"time":32343,"text":"and you'd study a scientific paper"},{"time":34463,"text":"in relation to medicine."},{"time":36304,"text":"And after week one, it was about cardiovascular mortality,"},{"time":39053,"text":"a dry subject -- how many people die of heart disease,"},{"time":42733,"text":"what the rates are."},{"time":44117,"text":"And they were competitive about this:"},{"time":46093,"text":"\"You pommies, your rates of heart disease are shocking.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":49189,"text":"And of course, they were right."},{"time":51085,"text":"Australians have about a third less heart disease than we do --"},{"time":55066,"text":"less deaths from heart attacks, heart failure, less strokes --"},{"time":58857,"text":"they're generally a healthier bunch."},{"time":60917,"text":"And of course they said this was because of"},{"time":62608,"text":"their fine moral standing, their exercise,"},{"time":64672,"text":"because they're Australians and we're weedy pommies, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68740,"text":"But it's not just Australia that has better health than Britain."},{"time":73771,"text":"Within Britain, there is a gradient of health --"},{"time":77299,"text":"and this is what's called standardized mortality,"},{"time":79235,"text":"basically your chances of dying."},{"time":81323,"text":"This is looking at data from the paper about 20 years ago,"},{"time":84667,"text":"but it's true today."},{"time":86142,"text":"Comparing your rates of dying 50 degrees north --"},{"time":89232,"text":"that's the South, that's London and places --"},{"time":91499,"text":"by latitude, and 55 degrees --"},{"time":94851,"text":"the bad news is that's here, Glasgow."},{"time":97235,"text":"I'm from Edinburgh. Worse news, that's even Edinburgh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100083,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104207,"text":"So what accounts for this horrible space here"},{"time":107513,"text":"between us up here in southern Scotland"},{"time":109717,"text":"and the South?"},{"time":110727,"text":"Now, we know about smoking,"},{"time":112145,"text":"deep-fried Mars bars, chips -- the Glasgow diet."},{"time":114847,"text":"All of these things."},{"time":116175,"text":"But this graph is after taking into account"},{"time":118967,"text":"all of these known risk factors."},{"time":121031,"text":"This is after accounting for smoking, social class, diet,"},{"time":124800,"text":"all those other known risk factors."},{"time":126543,"text":"We are left with this missing space"},{"time":128767,"text":"of increased deaths the further north you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132627,"text":"Now, sunlight, of course, comes into this."},{"time":135264,"text":"And vitamin D has had a great deal of press,"},{"time":137584,"text":"and a lot of people get concerned about it."},{"time":139586,"text":"And we need vitamin D. It's now a requirement that children have a certain amount."},{"time":143578,"text":"My grandmother grew up in Glasgow,"},{"time":145810,"text":"back in the 1920s and '30s when rickets was a real problem"},{"time":149396,"text":"and cod liver oil was brought in."},{"time":151594,"text":"And that really prevented the rickets that used to be common in this city."},{"time":155538,"text":"And I as a child was fed cod liver oil by my grandmother."},{"time":159458,"text":"I distinctly -- nobody forgets cod liver oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162482,"text":"But an association: The higher people's blood levels of vitamin D are,"},{"time":167264,"text":"the less heart disease they have, the less cancer."},{"time":170591,"text":"There seems to be a lot of data suggesting that vitamin D is very good for you."},{"time":174433,"text":"And it is, to prevent rickets and so on."},{"time":176727,"text":"But if you give people vitamin D supplements,"},{"time":179447,"text":"you don't change that high rate of heart disease."},{"time":182879,"text":"And the evidence for it preventing cancers is not yet great."},{"time":186607,"text":"So what I'm going to suggest is that vitamin D is not the only story in town."},{"time":191464,"text":"It's not the only reason preventing heart disease."},{"time":194775,"text":"High vitamin D levels, I think, are a marker for sunlight exposure,"},{"time":199144,"text":"and sunlight exposure, in methods I'm going to show,"},{"time":202359,"text":"is good for heart disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204798,"text":"Anyway, I came back from Australia,"},{"time":206759,"text":"and despite the obvious risks to my health, I moved to Aberdeen."},{"time":210255,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":212807,"text":"Now, in Aberdeen, I started my dermatology training."},{"time":215958,"text":"But I also became interested in research,"},{"time":217903,"text":"and in particular I became interested in this substance, nitric oxide."},{"time":221078,"text":"Now these three guys up here,"},{"time":222454,"text":"Furchgott, Ignarro and Murad,"},{"time":224024,"text":"won the Nobel Prize for medicine back in 1998."},{"time":227286,"text":"And they were the first people to describe"},{"time":229429,"text":"this new chemical transmitter, nitric oxide."},{"time":232774,"text":"What nitric oxide does is it dilates blood vessels,"},{"time":235799,"text":"so it lowers your blood pressure."},{"time":237670,"text":"It also dilates the coronary arteries, so it stops angina."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241837,"text":"And what was remarkable about it"},{"time":243223,"text":"was in the past when we think of chemical messengers within the body,"},{"time":247294,"text":"we thought of complicated things like estrogen and insulin,"},{"time":250464,"text":"or nerve transmission."},{"time":251934,"text":"Very complex processes with very complex chemicals"},{"time":255229,"text":"that fit into very complex receptors."},{"time":257517,"text":"And here's this incredibly simple molecule,"},{"time":259878,"text":"a nitrogen and an oxygen that are stuck together,"},{"time":263216,"text":"and yet these are hugely important for [unclear] our low blood pressure,"},{"time":267846,"text":"for neurotransmission, for many, many things,"},{"time":270452,"text":"but particularly cardiovascular health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273854,"text":"And I started doing research, and we found, very excitingly,"},{"time":277156,"text":"that the skin produces nitric oxide."},{"time":279766,"text":"So it's not just in the cardiovascular system it arises."},{"time":282663,"text":"It arises in the skin."},{"time":284530,"text":"Well, having found that and published that,"},{"time":286396,"text":"I thought, well, what's it doing?"},{"time":288452,"text":"How do you have low blood pressure in your skin?"},{"time":289932,"text":"It's not the heart. What do you do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292023,"text":"So I went off to the States, as many people do if they're going to do research,"},{"time":296094,"text":"and I spent a few years in Pittsburgh. This is Pittsburgh."},{"time":299831,"text":"And I was interested in these really complex systems."},{"time":302444,"text":"We thought that maybe nitric oxide affected cell death,"},{"time":306485,"text":"and how cells survive, and their resistance to other things."},{"time":308965,"text":"And I first off started work in cell culture, growing cells,"},{"time":312332,"text":"and then I was using knockout mouse models --"},{"time":314452,"text":"mice that couldn't make the gene."},{"time":316189,"text":"We worked out a mechanism, which -- NO was helping cells survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320599,"text":"And I then moved back to Edinburgh."},{"time":324420,"text":"And in Edinburgh, the experimental animal we use is the medical student."},{"time":327202,"text":"It's a species close to human,"},{"time":329260,"text":"with several advantages over mice:"},{"time":331162,"text":"They're free, you don't shave them, they feed themselves,"},{"time":334618,"text":"and nobody pickets your office saying,"},{"time":336738,"text":"\"Save the lab medical student.\""},{"time":339138,"text":"So they're really an ideal model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342401,"text":"But what we found"},{"time":344362,"text":"was that we couldn't reproduce in man the data we had shown in mice."},{"time":348979,"text":"It seemed we couldn't turn off the production"},{"time":352219,"text":"of nitric oxide in the skin of humans."},{"time":355299,"text":"We put on creams that blocked the enzyme that made it,"},{"time":358091,"text":"we injected things. We couldn't turn off the nitric oxide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362475,"text":"And the reason for this, it turned out, after two or three years' work,"},{"time":365739,"text":"was that in the skin we have huge stores"},{"time":369787,"text":"not of nitric oxide, because nitric oxide is a gas,"},{"time":372875,"text":"and it's released -- (Poof!) -- and in a few seconds it's away,"},{"time":376027,"text":"but it can be turned into these forms of nitric oxide --"},{"time":379251,"text":"nitrate, NO3; nitrite, NO2; nitrosothiols."},{"time":382883,"text":"And these are more stable,"},{"time":384299,"text":"and your skin has got really large stores of NO."},{"time":388459,"text":"And we then thought to ourselves, with those big stores,"},{"time":391284,"text":"I wonder if sunlight might activate those stores"},{"time":394595,"text":"and release them from the skin,"},{"time":396339,"text":"where the stores are about 10 times as big as what's in the circulation."},{"time":399731,"text":"Could the sun activate those stores into the circulation,"},{"time":402571,"text":"and there in the circulation do its good things for your cardiovascular system?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407811,"text":"Well, I'm an experimental dermatologist,"},{"time":410339,"text":"so what we did was we thought"},{"time":411644,"text":"we'd have to expose our experimental animals to sunlight."},{"time":415171,"text":"And so what we did was we took a bunch of volunteers"},{"time":419251,"text":"and we exposed them to ultraviolet light."},{"time":421949,"text":"So these are kind of sunlamps."},{"time":423678,"text":"Now, what we were careful to do was,"},{"time":426374,"text":"vitamin D is made by ultraviolet B rays"},{"time":429334,"text":"and we wanted to separate our story from the vitamin D story."},{"time":433310,"text":"So we used ultraviolet A, which doesn't make vitamin D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437157,"text":"When we put people under a lamp"},{"time":439438,"text":"for the equivalent of about 30 minutes of sunshine in summer in Edinburgh,"},{"time":444514,"text":"what we produced was, we produced a rise"},{"time":447054,"text":"in circulating nitric oxide."},{"time":449046,"text":"So we put patients with these subjects under the UV,"},{"time":451894,"text":"and their NO levels do go up,"},{"time":454310,"text":"and their blood pressure goes down."},{"time":456446,"text":"Not by much, as an individual level,"},{"time":458823,"text":"but enough at a population level"},{"time":461190,"text":"to shift the rates of heart disease in a whole population."},{"time":464910,"text":"And when we shone UV at them,"},{"time":467334,"text":"or when we warmed them up to the same level as the lamps,"},{"time":470996,"text":"but didn't actually let the rays hit the skin, this didn't happen."},{"time":474258,"text":"So this seems to be a feature of ultraviolet rays hitting the skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478122,"text":"Now, we're still collecting data."},{"time":479946,"text":"A few good things here:"},{"time":481394,"text":"This appeared to be more marked in older people."},{"time":484541,"text":"I'm not sure exactly how much."},{"time":486154,"text":"One of the subjects here was my mother-in-law,"},{"time":487927,"text":"and clearly I do not know her age."},{"time":490879,"text":"But certainly in people older than my wife,"},{"time":494311,"text":"this appears to be a more marked effect."},{"time":497444,"text":"And the other thing I should mention"},{"time":498695,"text":"was there was no change in vitamin D."},{"time":500751,"text":"This is separate from vitamin D."},{"time":502871,"text":"So vitamin D is good for you -- it stops rickets,"},{"time":504407,"text":"it prevents calcium metabolism, important stuff."},{"time":506647,"text":"But this is a separate mechanism from vitamin D."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509679,"text":"Now, one of the problems with looking at blood pressure"},{"time":512255,"text":"is your body does everything it can"},{"time":513807,"text":"to keep your blood pressure at the same place."},{"time":515390,"text":"If your leg is chopped off and you lose blood,"},{"time":517039,"text":"your body will clamp down, increase the heart rate,"},{"time":519944,"text":"do everything it can to keep your blood pressure up."},{"time":522168,"text":"That is an absolutely fundamental physiological principle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525144,"text":"So what we've next done"},{"time":526951,"text":"is we've moved on to looking at blood vessel dilatation."},{"time":530607,"text":"So we've measured -- this is again,"},{"time":532104,"text":"notice no tail and hairless, this is a medical student."},{"time":537432,"text":"In the arm, you can measure blood flow in the arm"},{"time":540050,"text":"by how much it swells up as some blood flows into it."},{"time":543282,"text":"And what we've shown is that doing a sham irradiation --"},{"time":546757,"text":"this is the thick line here --"},{"time":548226,"text":"this is shining UV on the arm so it warms up"},{"time":550626,"text":"but keeping it covered so the rays don't hit the skin."},{"time":553450,"text":"There is no change in blood flow, in dilatation of the blood vessels."},{"time":557362,"text":"But the active irradiation,"},{"time":559211,"text":"during the UV and for an hour after it,"},{"time":562563,"text":"there is dilation of the blood vessels."},{"time":564660,"text":"This is the mechanism by which you lower blood pressure,"},{"time":567260,"text":"by which you dilate the coronary arteries also,"},{"time":569636,"text":"to let the blood be supplied with the heart."},{"time":571347,"text":"So here, further data that ultraviolet -- that's sunlight --"},{"time":575740,"text":"has benefits on the blood flow and the cardiovascular system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580619,"text":"So we thought we'd just kind of model --"},{"time":582962,"text":"Different amounts of UV hit different parts of the Earth at different times of year,"},{"time":589211,"text":"so you can actually work out those stores of nitric oxide --"},{"time":593235,"text":"the nitrates, nitrites, nitrosothiols in the skin --"},{"time":595491,"text":"cleave to release NO."},{"time":598363,"text":"Different wavelengths of light have different activities of doing that."},{"time":602188,"text":"So you can look at the wavelengths of light that do that."},{"time":604267,"text":"And you can look -- So, if you live on the equator, the sun comes straight overhead,"},{"time":608252,"text":"it comes through a very thin bit of atmosphere."},{"time":610068,"text":"In winter or summer, it's the same amount of light."},{"time":612507,"text":"If you live up here, in summer"},{"time":615020,"text":"the sun is coming fairly directly down,"},{"time":617676,"text":"but in winter it's coming through a huge amount of atmosphere,"},{"time":620983,"text":"and much of the ultraviolet is weeded out,"},{"time":624204,"text":"and the range of wavelengths that hit the Earth"},{"time":626556,"text":"are different from summer to winter."},{"time":628884,"text":"So what you can do is you can multiply those data"},{"time":630826,"text":"by the NO that's released"},{"time":632819,"text":"and you can calculate how much nitric oxide"},{"time":636003,"text":"would be released from the skin into the circulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639172,"text":"Now, if you're on the equator here --"},{"time":641172,"text":"that's these two lines here, the red line and the purple line --"},{"time":644599,"text":"the amount of nitric oxide that's released is the area under the curve,"},{"time":648996,"text":"it's the area in this space here."},{"time":651027,"text":"So if you're on the equator, December or June,"},{"time":653724,"text":"you've got masses of NO being released from the skin."},{"time":656980,"text":"So Ventura is in southern California."},{"time":659444,"text":"In summer, you might as well be at the equator."},{"time":661660,"text":"It's great. Lots of NO is released."},{"time":663716,"text":"Ventura mid-winter, well, there's still a decent amount."},{"time":667659,"text":"Edinburgh in summer, the area beneath the curve is pretty good,"},{"time":671620,"text":"but Edinburgh in winter, the amount of NO that can be released"},{"time":675835,"text":"is next to nothing, tiny amounts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679693,"text":"So what do we think?"},{"time":681498,"text":"We're still working at this story,"},{"time":683090,"text":"we're still developing it, we're still expanding it."},{"time":685002,"text":"We think it's very important."},{"time":686650,"text":"We think it probably accounts for a lot of the north-south health divide within Britain,"},{"time":690243,"text":"It's of relevance to us."},{"time":691874,"text":"We think that the skin --"},{"time":693562,"text":"well, we know that the skin has got very large stores"},{"time":696450,"text":"of nitric oxide as these various other forms."},{"time":698674,"text":"We suspect a lot of these come from diet,"},{"time":700547,"text":"green leafy vegetables, beetroot, lettuce"},{"time":702818,"text":"has a lot of these nitric oxides that we think go to the skin."},{"time":706138,"text":"We think they're then stored in the skin,"},{"time":708282,"text":"and we think the sunlight releases this"},{"time":710682,"text":"where it has generally beneficial effects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713315,"text":"And this is ongoing work, but dermatologists --"},{"time":715794,"text":"I mean, I'm a dermatologist."},{"time":717514,"text":"My day job is saying to people, \"You've got skin cancer,"},{"time":720042,"text":"it's caused by sunlight, don't go in the sun.\""},{"time":721922,"text":"I actually think a far more important message"},{"time":724658,"text":"is that there are benefits as well as risks to sunlight."},{"time":728082,"text":"Yes, sunlight is the major alterable risk factor for skin cancer,"},{"time":733835,"text":"but deaths from heart disease are a hundred times higher"},{"time":736706,"text":"than deaths from skin cancer."},{"time":738658,"text":"And I think that we need to be more aware of,"},{"time":741307,"text":"and we need to find the risk-benefit ratio."},{"time":743386,"text":"How much sunlight is safe,"},{"time":744858,"text":"and how can we finesse this best for our general health?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":749058,"text":"So, thank you very much indeed."},{"time":751238,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}